title: RS-25 Space Shuttle Main Engine (SSME)
description: The RS-25, otherwise known as the Space Shuttle Main Engine (SSME), is a reusable liquid-fuel rocket engine built by Pratt & Whitney Rocketdyne for the Space Shuttle, running on liquid hydrogen and oxygen.

title: J-2 Saturn V Engine
description: Rocketdyne's J-2 rocket engine was a major component of the Saturn V used in the Apollo program to send men to the Moon.

title: RD-170 Rocket Engine-170
description: The RD-170 is the world's most powerful liquid-fuel rocket engine, designed and produced in the USSR by NPO Energomash for use with the Energia launch vehicle.
